abstract = {The short term and small-scale sea surface temperature prediction using deep learning has achieved good results. It is still an important challenge to obtain accurate large-scale and long-term SST predictions. In this study, we used a temporal convolutional network (TCN) to predict the SSTs of the Indian Ocean in the sea area of 40°E -110°E and 25°N to -25°S from 2014 to 2018 at a spatial resolution of 1°\texttimes{}1°. By using the observation data of the previous 10 years to forecast the monthly SSTs of the next 5 years, this study accomplished a 5-year forecast with one model, which had a monthly mean of the root mean square error (RMSE) of 0.506°C. In contrast, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration needs to constantly collect observation data and use seven models to make 5-year forecasts. The results showed that the predicted SST through the proposed TCN can better fit the long-term SST variation curve.},
